<title>USA: Laser Storm Inc 1996 fy earnings results.</title>
<headline>Laser Storm Inc 1996 fy earnings results.</headline>
<dateline>DENVER 1997-04-25</dateline>
<text>
<p>YEAR ENDED</p>
<p>						     December 31,</p>
<p>						1996		    1995</p>
<p> Net Sales			   $5,487,899	    $5,408,745</p>
<p> Cost of Goods Sold		 2,477,415	     2,323,471</p>
<p> Gross Profit			 3,010,484	     3,085,274</p>
<p>Retail Operations</p>
<p> Net sales				410,312		  68,404</p>
<p> Cost of sales			  151,661		  29,135</p>
<p>    Gross profit			258,269		  39,269</p>
<p>Expenses:</p>
<p> General and administrative     3,515,768	     1,523,038</p>
<p> Selling and marketing	    1,629,780		 820,471</p>
<p>Severance and terminations</p>
<p> costs				    248,768			 -</p>
<p> Depreciation and amortization    297,768		 116,183</p>
<p> Product development		  320,671		 139,979</p>
<p> Contingent settlements		     -		 270,000</p>
<p>    Total expenses		  6,021,696	     2,869,671</p>
<p> Operating Income (loss)	(2,743,561)		 254,872</p>
<p>Other Income (Expense)</p>
<p> Interest Income			 97,202		   2,282</p>
<p> Interest Expense		    (12,573)		 (9,252)</p>
<p> Loss on disposal of equipment   (86,934)		(16,054)</p>
<p>Income (Loss) Before</p>
<p> Income Taxes		     (2,745,866)		 231,848</p>
<p>    Income tax (expense)		    -		 (9,000)</p>
<p> Net Income (loss)		(2,745,866)		 222,848</p>
<p>Net Income (loss) Applicable</p>
<p> to Common Shareholders	 (2,791,756)		 204,848</p>
<p> Common Shares Outstanding	3,244,000	     2,033,000</p>
<p>Income (Loss) per share</p>
<p> applicable to common shareholders (0.86)		    0.10</p>
<p>NOTE: The company partially attributed its substantial loss, most of which was incurred in the fourth quarter of 1996, to the development of a new themed game, investigation of potential acquisitions, severance and termination costs and bad debts associated with the return of equipment from a single independent operator.</p>
<p>The company said it expects to incur additional operating losses of approximately $350,000 (unaudited) for the first quarter of 1997, of which  about $165,000 (unauditied) will be non-cash depreciation and amortization expenses.</p>
